      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">論語 2.21</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">Analects XXI.21</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>或謂孔子曰：「子奚不爲政？」子曰：「《書》云：『孝乎惟孝，友於兄弟。』施於有政，是亦爲政，奚其爲爲政？」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Some one addressed Confucius, saying, "Sir, why are you not engaged in the government?" The Master said, "What does the Shu-ching say of filial piety?—'You are filial, you discharge your brotherly duties. These qualities are displayed in government.' This then also constitutes the exercise of government. Why must there be that—making one be in the government?"</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="lunyu__book-02-weizheng__022__zhwikisource-20260529__legge-cc-v1-1893">
