      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">論語 2.22</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">Analects XXII.22</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>子曰：「人而無信，不知其可也。大車無輗，小車無軏，其何以行之哉？」</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The Master said, "I do not know how a man without truthfulness is to get on. How can a large carriage be made to go without the cross-bar for yoking the oxen to, or a small carriage without the arrangement for yoking the horses?"</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="lunyu__book-02-weizheng__023__zhwikisource-20260529__legge-cc-v1-1893">
